02:20.000 --> 02:22.514
Tom Lincoln!
It's a comin'

02:23.520 --> 02:26.592
- Boy or gal?
- 'T aint fur enough along yit fer a tag.

02:27.120 --> 02:30.192
- How's Nancy standin' it?
- She's a-prayin'

02:35.440 --> 02:36.953
It's a boy?

02:37.280 --> 02:38.759
It's as long as an eel!

02:45.000 --> 02:49.835
Shucks, he'never
amount to nothin' nohow!

02:51.000 --> 02:52.558
Is he purty?

02:53.160 --> 02:56.436
Homely as a mud fence!

02:57.400 --> 02:59.675
What do you 'low
to call him, Aunty?

03:04.880 --> 03:06.791
Abraham.

03:33.120 --> 03:36.855
There he is. Ugliest, laziest,
smartest man in New Salem.

03:36.890 --> 03:40.591
- Ain't yuh, Abe?
- I don't mind my face, I'm behind it.

03:40.720 --> 03:42.870
It's the people
in front that get jarred.

03:44.720 --> 03:48.110
Whip any man in shoo
leather I At least, I hope he can.

03:48.720 --> 03:50.950
Offut does the braggin'
I do the runnin'

03:51.240 --> 03:53.231
You better dust off
them shoes then, stranger,

03:53.600 --> 03:54.874
'cause you ain't here for long.

03:55.320 --> 03:57.231
Well, I was aimin'
to settle here awhile.

03:57.600 --> 04:00.797
- This ain't no peaceable town.
- Well, I'm a peaceable man.

04:01.120 --> 04:02.712
Wait till
Jack Armstrong gets hold o' yuh.

04:03.040 --> 04:05.713
He'll throw yuh out
that door like yuh was a sack o' meal!

04:06.360 --> 04:07.918
- Big fellow?
- No bigger'n you,

04:08.240 --> 04:11.949
but he's champeen o' this country
he ain' never been licked.

04:12.360 --> 04:14.078
And when he sees you...

04:14.200 --> 04:16.918
Folks can't even spit
without his sayso.

04:18.079 --> 04:19.957
Chuck me outa that door, you say?

04:20.240 --> 04:21.673
Like a sack o' meal.

04:23.840 --> 04:26.559
Well, that's a pretty long
chuck for a peaceful man.

04:28.440 --> 04:29.759
Whar be he?

04:30.080 --> 04:32.469
Now, Armstrong,
cain't you leave us be?

04:32.680 --> 04:34.910
Yuh just busted up
old man Simpson's place

04:35.080 --> 04:37.640
and scattered
his new place all over the county.

04:37.720 --> 04:39.676
Man, don't you ever rest?

04:39.920 --> 04:44.789
Whare be he?
That yellow-livered baboon from Indianny!

04:45.560 --> 04:48.870
I come from Indianny,
but not that part.

04:49.240 --> 04:50.639
Well, get down!

04:51.440 --> 04:54.318
Let's see what bones
I wants to crack first!

05:02.840 --> 05:04.068
Get a good hold, Jack!

05:04.240 --> 05:05.559
Come on,
an' get yer neck broke!

05:06.880 --> 05:08.108
This is the neatest
wrestle you've ever had.

05:08.240 --> 05:09.355
Go to him, Champ!

05:09.560 --> 05:11.551
- Get 'in, Jack!
- Abraham Lincoln!

05:12.000 --> 05:15.356
- Let's get 'im, Abe come on!
- Get 'in, Jack!

05:16.600 --> 05:21.549
- Get 'im, Jack!
- Atta boy, Abe!

05:21.880 --> 05:24.189
I'll bet yuh ten dollars,
Offut, on the Champeen!

05:24.520 --> 05:26.317
- Watch 'im, boy!
- Git 'im!

05:26.520 --> 05:28.795
- Watch 'im, boy!
- Come on, git 'im!

05:29.760 --> 05:32.115
- Come on, git 'im!
- Git 'im!

05:33.920 --> 05:35.638
Watch 'im, boy!

05:37.640 --> 05:39.915
Come on, git 'im!

05:56.360 --> 05:57.634
Now, come on, all o' you.

05:57.800 --> 05:59.392
I'm the big tuck of thisn lick!

05:59.520 --> 06:00.953
Yuh are, eh?

06:03.080 --> 06:04.308
Hold on, boys!

06:04.920 --> 06:06.239
He throwed me fair.

06:07.880 --> 06:09.313
What's your name?

06:10.160 --> 06:12.913
Lincoln,...
Abraham Lincoln.

06:13.800 --> 06:15.756
Well, we're goin' to make yuh one of us.

06:16.400 --> 06:18.231
Come on, boys, I'll set 'em up!

06:18.520 --> 06:19.873
It's about time you set 'em up.

06:25.120 --> 06:27.315
Let's have some o'
that rattlesnake bite.

06:28.120 --> 06:29.633
He said he was a peaceful man.

06:30.080 --> 06:31.877
He meant peaceful like a wildcat!

06:32.000 --> 06:33.433
Yeh, that's what he thought.

06:34.600 --> 06:36.238
Looks like good corn liquor.

06:36.520 --> 06:38.112
That is corn liquor.

06:40.520 --> 06:42.112
Come on, Abe. Where's yours?

06:42.640 --> 06:44.358
No, I don't care much for it.

06:44.480 --> 06:46.357
Come on, have a drink, Abe.

06:47.240 --> 06:49.231
Well, I'll drink
if you'll take it like I do.

06:49.640 --> 06:50.789
How's that?

06:51.520 --> 06:53.590
Lift up the barrel,
and drink it outa the bung.

06:55.680 --> 06:56.908
Well, I'll show you boys.

06:58.840 --> 07:02.674
Maybe can, maybe can't.
Try it, anyway.

07:19.440 --> 07:20.873
Whew!

07:22.400 --> 07:24.197
He's the strongest man in Salem!

07:24.520 --> 07:26.351
I told you he was the strongest man.

07:26.560 --> 07:29.233
I've seen him lift
500 pounds in each hand.

07:32.240 --> 07:34.276
- Ain't yuh drinkin?
- No.

07:35.400 --> 07:36.958
- Teetotal?
- No.

07:37.600 --> 07:38.874
Reformer?

07:39.360 --> 07:41.749
No, I don't
regulate nobody's drinkin'

07:42.560 --> 07:43.754
just my own.

07:45.000 --> 07:47.560
I've seen him lift a thousand...

07:50.360 --> 07:53.432
- In this sense,-
- the term "law" -

07:54.360 --> 07:59.559
- includes any edict,-
- decree, order,-

08:00.320 --> 08:05.633
- ordinance,-
- statute, resolutión,-

08:06.360 --> 08:09.033
rule, etcetera. -

08:10.200 --> 08:13.749
¡Uff!, etcetera...

08:20.240 --> 08:23.869
Well, my old Daddy
taught me how to work,

08:24.080 --> 08:25.877
but he never
taught me how to like it.

08:29.400 --> 08:32.119
I reckon I better
keep on with the lesson.

08:33.360 --> 08:35.828
I'd rather keep on
with something else.

08:36.440 --> 08:40.831
You made a bad bargain
making me the professor.

08:41.240 --> 08:43.390
Well he told me about that too.

08:44.240 --> 08:46.390
He said:
"When you make a bad bargain,

08:47.560 --> 08:49.118
hug it all the tighter".

08:51.080 --> 08:53.958
But he didn't mean
this kind of a bargain.

08:55.560 --> 08:59.314
Well, don't you like it,
Ann, when I hold you tight?

09:02.680 --> 09:05.399
I guess every girl sorta likes that...

09:08.000 --> 09:12.232
Now, Abe, what is law?

09:13.520 --> 09:20.039
Well, professor, law is a rule
of human conduct governing

09:20.280 --> 09:21.554
Whoa!

09:23.440 --> 09:28.594
Abe, I'ain't payin' you no forty
cents a day to spark a pretty gal!

09:29.080 --> 09:31.640
Well, Uncle Jimmie,
I don't charge nothing extra for it

09:31.800 --> 09:33.028
just throw it in.

09:36.880 --> 09:39.872
I'm expectin'
a sight of rails cut of you.

09:40.720 --> 09:42.597
He's the best
rail-splitter in the country.

09:43.240 --> 09:45.674
He'll be more than a rail-splitter.

09:47.040 --> 09:48.712
How old are you, Uncle Jimmie?

09:49.960 --> 09:51.359
Oh nearin' forty.

09:52.160 --> 09:55.277
I'll get you out forty
more rails than you expected.

09:58.240 --> 10:01.915
Giddap! Maybe you'd better
make it nearin' seventy!

10:13.720 --> 10:17.952
Now, Abe,
your professor needs a seat

10:18.120 --> 10:20.918
where's there's more law
and less temptatión.

10:27.080 --> 10:29.036
Oh, Abe! Ohhh!

10:31.000 --> 10:33.036
Ohhhh!

10:34.080 --> 10:36.071
- Are you all right, Anne?
- I think so.

10:36.240 --> 10:39.198
- Are you hurt?
- My legs are still on me.

10:42.360 --> 10:44.078
Scared me worse than it did you.

10:44.520 --> 10:45.953
Did it, Abe?

10:47.960 --> 10:53.876
You know, Anne, if anything happened
to you, I don't think I could live.

10:55.000 --> 10:58.788
Funny, Abe, I feel the same about you.

11:00.680 --> 11:02.318
You taught me how to love.

11:03.800 --> 11:06.109
Have I taught you to like it?

11:15.440 --> 11:22.630
In the gloaming, oh, my darling,-

11:23.080 --> 11:31.237
When the lights are dim and low,-

11:32.160 --> 11:36.950
And the quiet shadows falling. -

11:37.160 --> 11:46.239
Softly come and softly go. -

11:47.880 --> 11:49.632
It's awful nice this time of day.

11:50.440 --> 11:51.873
Yes, Abe.

11:52.320 --> 11:54.550
Can I tell you
a sort of a story, Anne?

11:54.920 --> 11:57.150
Why of course, Abe.

11:57.360 --> 12:00.318
Well, there was
a town in lllinois called...

12:01.360 --> 12:02.588
called...

12:02.680 --> 12:04.796
- New Salem?
- Yeh, that's it.

12:05.520 --> 12:09.035
And in that town lived
the prettiest girl in the worid.

12:09.520 --> 12:10.953
What was her name?

12:11.240 --> 12:12.559
Anne Rutledge.

12:13.200 --> 12:14.553
Oh, Abe...

12:17.240 --> 12:20.038
What I'd like
to find out about that girl is,

12:20.760 --> 12:24.799
she ever take a little time off
to think about gettin' married?

12:25.440 --> 12:27.112
Well, maybe.

12:27.520 --> 12:30.512
'Cause there's an Abe Lincoln
hanging around that's a pretty good catch.

12:31.120 --> 12:32.473
What's he like?

12:33.240 --> 12:37.870
Oh, he's a big merchant,
owner of three stores all bankrupt.

12:38.400 --> 12:41.119
Well, is he handsome?

12:43.360 --> 12:46.591
His pa said that Abe
had been cut out with an axe.

12:46.840 --> 12:48.876
Politician too, I hear.

12:49.760 --> 12:52.558
Yes, he's got less property
and owes more debts

12:52.760 --> 12:54.830
than anybody
ever running for the legislature.

12:55.520 --> 12:58.796
Oh, Abe, you'll do all
right when you get started.

13:03.400 --> 13:07.632
There's something I'd like to start
right now if I thought I could finish it.

13:09.320 --> 13:10.719
You know, Anne, I...

13:11.360 --> 13:13.430
I've always done a lot of dreamin'

13:14.680 --> 13:16.955
and lately it seems when I dream,

13:18.280 --> 13:20.475
your face gets mixed up in it.

13:22.600 --> 13:28.072
Does it really, Abe?
Tell me about the mixin'

13:29.160 --> 13:35.156
I feel as though I'm going to be
seeing your face till the day I die.

13:39.160 --> 13:43.551
'Course I know that would be pretty hard
for you to have to look at my face that long.

13:44.520 --> 13:46.670
Everybody to their own opinión

13:49.160 --> 13:50.559
Meaning?

13:52.960 --> 13:54.473
I think...

13:54.920 --> 14:00.790
it's the dearest, kindest,
most beautiful face in the whole worid!

14:00.920 --> 14:05.232
Oh, Anne...
Anne...

14:09.800 --> 14:12.792
I know
that's just flattery but I love it.

14:14.720 --> 14:17.712
You know
I feel like little Jimmie Watkins,

14:17.920 --> 14:20.070
he got a hunk of gingerbread
the other day and says:

14:20.320 --> 14:23.437
"I guess there's nobody
likes ginger bread like I does and

14:25.600 --> 14:26.953
gets so little of it".

14:27.760 --> 14:29.273
Oh, Abe!

14:31.840 --> 14:33.193
Anne, will you...

14:34.480 --> 14:35.799
will you marry me?

14:37.320 --> 14:38.799
I mean, of course when I...

14:39.040 --> 14:41.759
when I...
get out of debt and can support you?

14:42.880 --> 14:48.238
Well, you know, Abe,
I've intended to for a long while

14:49.920 --> 14:53.674
that is, of course, if you asked me.

14:54.920 --> 14:58.629
You... you mean?

14:59.040 --> 15:04.034
Yes, Abe, you've got your gingerbread.

15:06.160 --> 15:07.798
Oh, Anne!

15:12.840 --> 15:24.069
Will you think of me and love me-

15:24.920 --> 15:35.034
As you did once long ago?-

15:40.080 --> 15:41.354
How is she, Doctor?

15:41.920 --> 15:43.194
Pretty bad.

15:45.720 --> 15:47.472
She's been asking for you, Abe.

15:47.800 --> 15:49.233
I came as soon as I could.

15:51.000 --> 15:53.833
I had the fever pretty bad myself.

16:00.680 --> 16:03.638
I've got to tell you the truth, Abe,

16:04.360 --> 16:06.078
It's hopeless...

16:08.280 --> 16:09.759
perhaps by tomorrow...

16:11.160 --> 16:12.912
no longer.

16:39.760 --> 16:43.958
I'm so glad you came, Abe.

16:46.160 --> 16:48.037
Are you all right now?

16:48.200 --> 16:51.954
Now, don't bother about me, dear.
I'm all right now.

16:54.160 --> 17:00.190
I know the truth, dear.
It's good-bye.

17:00.760 --> 17:04.719
No, no, Anne dear,
you're not going to leave me!

17:05.440 --> 17:06.667
I won't let you!

17:07.440 --> 17:11.115
We must be brave, dear...

17:15.079 --> 17:19.278
Don't take me away!
Don't take me away!

17:21.000 --> 17:26.313
It's so dark and lonesome going!

17:26.560 --> 17:29.233
Anne, you mustn't let go!

17:31.760 --> 17:37.118
If they'd sing,
I wouldn't be so afraid.

17:40.000 --> 17:46.189
In the sweet by and by,-

17:46.680 --> 17:52.232
We shall meet on that beautiful shore. -

17:52.520 --> 17:56.559
We will meet there, dear.

17:57.520 --> 17:59.476
Oh... I love you so!

18:01.080 --> 18:04.117
I love you so!

18:42.440 --> 18:43.714
Feeling any better, Bowling?

18:44.400 --> 18:45.833
No, not much.

18:46.360 --> 18:49.432
I'll tell you, Doctor,
he's just like a sick child...

18:49.720 --> 18:52.632
He was lost for five days
before we found him.

18:52.760 --> 18:54.125
Yeh, I know.

18:54.160 --> 18:59.188
We took his pocket-knife away from him,
we were so afeard something might happen.

19:01.040 --> 19:04.077
Good gracious,
Abe, you're looking better!

19:16.000 --> 19:17.672
No use trying to talk to him,

19:18.160 --> 19:19.878
he just cain't answer.

19:41.000 --> 19:44.117
If we could only think of something
that would just bring him back.

19:47.080 --> 19:49.116
I guess time's the only thing.

19:52.160 --> 19:57.109
Why should the spirit of mortal be proud,

19:58.360 --> 20:02.672
like a swift-fleeting meteor,
fast-flying cloud?

20:04.240 --> 20:08.028
Flash of the lightning,
break of the wave,

20:10.720 --> 20:13.837
He passes from life
to his rest in the grave.

20:24.680 --> 20:26.591
My goodness, Mary Todd, just think!

20:26.880 --> 20:30.111
He'll be here in a few minutes
the catch of America!

20:30.360 --> 20:32.476
Stephen A. Douglas!

20:33.520 --> 20:35.476
Just think of being his wife!

20:35.800 --> 20:37.279
Don't be in such a hurry, sister.

20:37.400 --> 20:40.198
I'm not even engaged
much less married.

20:41.040 --> 20:42.598
But if he should propose?

20:43.360 --> 20:46.557
How do I know he's going further
than anyone else in Springfield?

20:47.520 --> 20:50.910
When I pick a husband, sister,
I'll pick a man!

20:51.320 --> 20:52.878
But I don't know
what you're talking about.

20:53.320 --> 20:57.359
A lot of people seem to think
a man named Abraham Lincoln

20:57.800 --> 20:59.711
is going even further than Mr. Douglas.

20:59.880 --> 21:02.474
Why, Mary Todd, have you gone crazy?

21:03.240 --> 21:06.949
You compare an unknown cornfield lawyer

21:07.120 --> 21:10.749
with a brilliant cultured gentleman
like Stephen A. Douglas!

21:10.880 --> 21:12.711
Why, if you just saw
the two of them together.

21:12.920 --> 21:14.239
Oh, he's here!

21:14.480 --> 21:17.313
Mr. Douglas is down in the parlor
and he's asking for Mary!

21:18.160 --> 21:20.310
Now, Mary, you must be
very careful, and remember

21:20.560 --> 21:22.312
he doesn't like to have giris too bold.

21:22.520 --> 21:25.671
Don't get so excited,
sister, and don't hurry me.

21:26.440 --> 21:28.158
I'll take care of myself.

21:56.960 --> 21:59.997
You glide through the dance
like grace itself Miss Todd.

22:00.320 --> 22:02.959
Always the politician, Mr. Douglas!

22:06.680 --> 22:10.593
Who wouldn't be a politician
with so fair a constituent to win?

22:54.440 --> 22:57.557
- Exquisite!
- The fan, Mr. Douglas?

22:57.680 --> 22:59.989
No, the fair owner herself.

23:05.400 --> 23:06.913
- May I look?
- Sr. Douglas...

23:07.920 --> 23:10.036
I wonder if you'd do me a great favor?

23:10.800 --> 23:11.994
Yes.

23:12.760 --> 23:15.035
Then, pray present me
to this young lady.

23:16.680 --> 23:18.193
- Miss Todd?
- Yes?

23:18.800 --> 23:23.237
May I present one
of the leading lawyers of Springfield

23:24.680 --> 23:26.193
Mr. Abraham Lincoln?

23:27.560 --> 23:28.879
Mr. Lincoln!

23:34.360 --> 23:37.397
Miss Todd I wonder
if you'd honor me with the next dance?

23:38.400 --> 23:41.312
Why,... why...

23:43.880 --> 23:45.552
I'd be delighted.

23:50.000 --> 23:52.230
Miss Todd, you thought my face was funny,

23:52.480 --> 23:53.993
and the way I dressed even funnier,

23:54.240 --> 23:55.514
but the joke's on you.

23:57.000 --> 23:58.399
Why, I don't understand.

23:59.520 --> 24:01.078
Wait till you dance with me.

24:31.360 --> 24:33.157
Have you got the license, Mr. Lincoln?

24:43.960 --> 24:45.188
Well, she got you.

24:45.680 --> 24:48.148
I knew she would
when she started out the first time for you.

24:48.440 --> 24:49.668
Now, Billie, don't bother me.

24:49.800 --> 24:51.836
I'm going to be married
and I'm scared to death.

24:53.000 --> 24:54.194
Oh, don't be alarmed.

24:54.400 --> 24:56.436
There's many a bite
that's worse than a bride's.

24:57.160 --> 25:00.391
But, Billie,
that woman scares me.

25:04.000 --> 25:07.834
She's even got the ridiculous idea
that I could get to be president.

25:08.000 --> 25:09.956
Oh, don't take that seriously.

25:10.240 --> 25:13.118
Every spunky girl thinks
that her husband ought to be president.

25:13.600 --> 25:15.556
I know, Billie,
but it's a pity to fool her.

25:15.960 --> 25:17.473
And she's a fine woman,

25:17.760 --> 25:19.910
smart as pepper and pretty too.

25:20.160 --> 25:21.878
She'll be a great help to you, Mr. Lincoln,

25:22.120 --> 25:24.111
but you've got to keep
climbing with her.

25:24.760 --> 25:26.876
Yes... yes, I know.

25:27.920 --> 25:30.036
I've got the best supper
you've ever tasted

25:30.280 --> 25:33.033
and the cake...

25:33.520 --> 25:35.033
wait till you see that cake!

25:35.240 --> 25:37.117
What can have happened
to Mr. Lincoln? It's long after the...

25:37.240 --> 25:39.310
He would be late at his own wedding.

25:40.320 --> 25:41.548
Now, never mind, Mary,

25:41.760 --> 25:44.194
if he doesn't come soon,
I'll send John after him.

25:44.280 --> 25:45.952
But he's hours late already!

25:46.240 --> 25:47.468
Think of that!

25:47.600 --> 25:50.068
Sister, calm yourself.

25:52.280 --> 25:54.191
For heaven's sakes,
you've got to hurry!

25:55.960 --> 25:59.873
Billie, you... you go ahead.
You go on over and I'll come later.

26:01.040 --> 26:04.271
I doubt if there's a word in the
dictionary that could tell how I feel!

26:04.680 --> 26:08.639
Billie, what does a man do
if his head's all right

26:08.840 --> 26:10.319
but his legs are cowardly?

26:10.440 --> 26:11.873
My cure is to get drunk.

26:12.840 --> 26:15.718
My legs are too frightened
to pay any attentión to liquor.

26:16.280 --> 26:17.952
I'll go ahead and
tell them that you're coming.

26:31.280 --> 26:32.474
Anne!

26:37.720 --> 26:38.869
Anne!

26:43.160 --> 26:44.388
Anne!

26:48.880 --> 26:51.474
We looked, everywhere,
tort we can't find him.

26:51.680 --> 26:53.955
No, can't find him...
not at the office.

26:54.240 --> 26:55.639
What on earth happened to him?

26:55.840 --> 26:57.751
He was in a terrible
state when I left him.

26:58.000 --> 27:01.231
He was so frightened and upset.
I imagine he just ran away.

27:01.480 --> 27:05.792
Ran away... from me!
On our weddin' day!

27:06.000 --> 27:07.194
Now sistern dear...

27:07.360 --> 27:08.554
Don't 'sister' me!

27:08.720 --> 27:13.794
Can you imagine! That's what a Todd gets
for engagin' herself to a country baboon!

27:14.040 --> 27:16.554
- Listen, dear, you mustn't...
- You may as well all go home!

27:17.200 --> 27:19.236
You hear me?
You may as well all go home!

27:19.560 --> 27:20.788
Not goin' to be any weddin' here.

27:20.920 --> 27:22.558
You can all go home
as far as I'm concerned!

27:23.920 --> 27:25.797
But this is so distressing!

27:30.760 --> 27:32.796
You certainly are a matchmaker

27:33.320 --> 27:36.073
to reconcile those two after
what happened two years ago.

27:36.160 --> 27:37.878
We all like Mr. Lincoln,

27:38.120 --> 27:40.714
and Mary is just
the girl to push him along.

27:42.200 --> 27:44.634
Oh, Mary, how sweet you look!

27:44.840 --> 27:46.034
What a lovely dress!

27:46.240 --> 27:48.470
Yes, and so becoming to her too.

27:49.000 --> 27:50.718
Maybe that's Mr. Lincoln now.

27:51.400 --> 27:54.870
Julia it all seems so strange
having things end this way.

27:55.240 --> 27:58.437
It's just as it should end. You and
Mr. Lincoln will make a great man.

28:00.360 --> 28:02.351
Good morning, Mr. Lincoln.

28:02.920 --> 28:04.114
Good morning.

28:07.280 --> 28:09.919
Come, my dear
we'll leave the happy pair alone.

28:10.240 --> 28:11.389
Good morning, Mary.

28:14.960 --> 28:18.396
I,... I...

28:22.240 --> 28:25.630
Mary, you don't have
to bother about me any more.

28:26.000 --> 28:28.036
I think I've settled down at last.

28:29.120 --> 28:32.192
I hope I can make
your future all you desire.

28:32.600 --> 28:34.795
We'll say no more about it, Mr. Lincoln.

28:35.880 --> 28:39.111
I really think, after all, you need me.

28:42.480 --> 28:45.119
You'll need a lot of patience
to put up with me, Mary,

28:46.200 --> 28:49.909
but if anyone can do it,
I'm sure you're the one.

28:54.160 --> 28:55.388
Oh, Mary!

29:30.920 --> 29:33.150
Douglas is a prize speaker,

29:33.360 --> 29:37.035
but just wait till old Abe
gets ahold of him on slavery!

29:37.360 --> 29:38.634
You're crazy!

29:38.760 --> 29:42.673
Lincoln has no more chance of beating
Douglas for Senate than I have.

29:43.520 --> 29:45.556
He only went to school for three months.

30:03.880 --> 30:08.192
There must be no issue of slavery.

30:12.040 --> 30:14.873
We must face the facts.

30:20.600 --> 30:26.596
I'll run Mr. Lincoln out of this campaign.

30:31.480 --> 30:33.391
I will not throw mud.

30:41.520 --> 30:49.234
Let each State mind its own business
and this Republic can exist forever...

30:50.000 --> 30:54.551
divided into free and slave states.

31:06.280 --> 31:11.957
We will not allow
the extensión of slavery to any State.

31:14.800 --> 31:18.713
We will not allow
the secessión of any State.

31:21.440 --> 31:29.074
Above all and before all,
the Unión must be preserved.

31:34.920 --> 31:39.596
A house divided
against itself must fall!

31:49.160 --> 31:52.755
- Douglas elected!-
- Hurrah for Douglas!-

31:53.080 --> 31:56.755
- Douglas elected!-
- Hurrah for Douglas!-

31:57.480 --> 32:04.670
- Douglas elected!-
- Hurrah for Douglas!-

32:19.040 --> 32:20.189
Mary...

32:28.840 --> 32:30.239
I'm home, Mary.

32:36.840 --> 32:39.070
You must be tired, Mr, Lincoln.

32:41.560 --> 32:42.754
Sit down.

32:54.200 --> 32:58.591
You just ait right here.
I'll get your supper for you in a minute.

33:13.680 --> 33:16.513
Billy, I feel like
the little boy who stubbed his toe.

33:16.680 --> 33:19.478
It hurt too bad to laugh,
and he was too big to cry.

33:21.920 --> 33:24.992
I'm fifty years old, Billy,
and a failure in everything.

33:25.920 --> 33:28.593
If I died today,
nobody'd ever know I'd lived.

33:30.880 --> 33:32.074
Come in.

33:36.760 --> 33:39.513
Mr. Lincoln,
I want you to meet Mr. Pell

33:39.960 --> 33:43.157
one of the most important
men in Eastern politics.

33:43.920 --> 33:46.673
- I'm pleased to meet you, Mr. Pell.
- I'm honored, indeed, Mr. Lincoln.

33:46.840 --> 33:49.434
- Meet my partner, Mr, Herndon.
- How do you do, Mr. Herndon?

33:49.560 --> 33:50.709
Happy to meet you, sir.

33:51.040 --> 33:53.076
- Won't you sit down, gentlemen?
- Thank you.

33:53.800 --> 33:58.271
Mr. Lincoln, your campaign against
Douglas has made you a national figure.

33:59.160 --> 34:03.119
I'm here to ask you if you will consider
being the Republican party's candidate

34:03.520 --> 34:05.078
for the presidency.

34:12.280 --> 34:15.033
Did you say a failure in everything?

34:19.600 --> 34:21.431
- A telegram for you, Mr. Fell.
- Oh thank you.

34:29.120 --> 34:31.714
Mr. Lincoln, you know
ever since John Brown's raid,

34:32.520 --> 34:35.795
the South has been infuriated,
the East on the verge of revolt,

34:35.920 --> 34:38.275
and now New York
threatens to quit the Unión.

34:38.440 --> 34:40.271
No, no New York mustn't do that.

34:40.760 --> 34:44.435
We must keep the front door on the hinge.
There can be no secessión.

34:46.800 --> 34:49.155
The Unión must be preserved.

34:49.600 --> 34:54.799
The crisis is at hand, Mr. Lincoln,
and we believe you are the man.

35:00.120 --> 35:04.398
Gentlemen,
I feel deeply grateful.

35:06.480 --> 35:09.552
Paw, Maw says if you don't come on home,
you won't get no supper.

35:10.240 --> 35:15.394
"I have another crisis; the soup and
the country are boiling over together!"

35:15.760 --> 35:17.318
Maw's boiling too!

35:21.120 --> 35:23.315
It needs deep consideratión.

35:24.280 --> 35:27.989
Well, Mr. Lincoln,
mayn't we meet you at our hotel later?

35:30.720 --> 35:32.836
- I'll be there within the hour?
- Thank you.

35:33.240 --> 35:36.152
Come on, Paw, we're hungry.

35:54.200 --> 35:57.272
They've started it.
This is gonna mean war!

35:57.400 --> 35:59.152
This darkio saw it himself.

35:59.600 --> 36:03.878
Brown and a gang of Abolxitionists
have captured the armory at Harper's Ferry!

36:04.400 --> 36:07.358
They're arming the slaves
to rise up and murder us all.

36:07.600 --> 36:10.160
They gived us all rifles.

36:10.320 --> 36:11.594
And what'd you do with yours?

36:11.800 --> 36:17.796
What'd I do? I trowed it down,
and I say, 'Feet, you travel'

36:18.120 --> 36:20.998
- They can't invade Virginia.
- No!

36:21.200 --> 36:23.760
Boys, go home and git your guns.

36:23.960 --> 36:25.154
What's all this talk about guns?

36:25.320 --> 36:26.958
This thing has gone far enough.

36:27.160 --> 36:29.913
We'll be murdered
in our beds by our own slaves.

36:30.080 --> 36:33.356
Pardon me, ladies,
while I find out about this desecratión.

36:33.480 --> 36:35.869
- John Brown, eh?
- Abolitionists!

36:36.080 --> 36:37.229
It's an outrage!

36:37.360 --> 36:39.271
Outrage isn't the word.

36:40.360 --> 36:46.754
I'll shoot on sight every Abolitionist
who dares defile the soil of old Virginia.

36:47.440 --> 36:50.273
- Who's he?
- That's the actor, John Wilkes Booth.

36:50.600 --> 36:52.750
He can't act
but the women don't know it.

36:53.080 --> 36:57.392
All right, men, get your guns
and we'll meet at the square!

36:57.800 --> 37:01.270
At the square!

37:34.840 --> 37:36.796
Can't say much for her dispositión!

37:37.040 --> 37:38.393
Hush! She may hear you.

37:38.560 --> 37:40.949
Soldiers, indeed!
They can't even carry trunks.

37:41.200 --> 37:43.430
Here you no, the stupid-looking one

37:43.640 --> 37:46.598
put that over there...
and you... idiot

37:46.760 --> 37:49.194
don't look at me like
a duck in a thunderstorm!

37:50.640 --> 37:52.710
Hurry... hurry!
Will you put them in there?

37:53.240 --> 37:55.276
I never saw such a lot of incompetents.

37:55.680 --> 37:58.194
And as for you with the whiskers,
I told you to put it in there.

38:00.080 --> 38:01.638
Oh, is it going to take forever?

38:05.320 --> 38:07.231
Thank heavens, that's the last!

38:08.280 --> 38:09.554
Imbeciles!

38:10.440 --> 38:11.839
Well, Mary, we're here.

38:12.160 --> 38:15.869
Thanks to me! If it wasn't for my advice,
you'd be out in Oregon, chopping trees.

38:16.440 --> 38:18.510
Yes, you're always right, Mary.

38:25.120 --> 38:27.315
I've found out one thing, Lincoln.

38:28.320 --> 38:30.709
Servants here are no better
than they are in Springfield.

38:33.440 --> 38:36.034
This place
hasn't been cleaned in a year.

38:38.920 --> 38:41.070
Why, Mr. President!

38:44.320 --> 38:45.548
Huh?

38:51.880 --> 38:55.919
Then we agree that the situatión
of our country is ominous.

38:56.080 --> 38:57.991
- Most alarming.
- Certainly.

38:58.160 --> 39:01.789
We agree that we must yield
to the demands of the South

39:02.840 --> 39:05.479
and evacuate Fort Sumter.

39:06.320 --> 39:08.231
- Absolutely.
- It's the only solutión.

39:08.480 --> 39:09.799
That must be done.

39:09.880 --> 39:14.271
We agree that our President
must be firmly guided by us.

39:15.920 --> 39:21.472
That we must make every effort
to control his inexperienced judgment.

39:22.280 --> 39:25.556
- We certainly must.
- Yes.

39:31.360 --> 39:32.634
Gentlemen...

39:32.760 --> 39:34.716
- Mr. President.
- Good morning, Mr. President.

39:34.880 --> 39:36.154
Thank you, Hay.

40:14.520 --> 40:15.873
Thank you, gentlemen...

40:17.240 --> 40:25.796
I will shoulder all responsibilities.
The relief shall go to Fort Sumter.

40:27.480 --> 40:29.198
That means war.

40:30.320 --> 40:34.552
Mr. Seward, I am a man of peace,

40:36.160 --> 40:39.277
but the Unión shall be preserved.

41:07.080 --> 41:08.877
Seventy-five thousand...

41:10.560 --> 41:13.233
It might be difficult
to get that many volunteers.

42:13.520 --> 42:21.518
- Glory, glory Hallelujah,-
- Glory, glory Hallelujah!-

42:21.880 --> 42:29.878
- Glory, glory Hallelujah!-
- His soul is marching on!-

42:31.000 --> 42:38.759
- Glory, glory Hallelujah,-
- Glory, glory Hallelujah!-

42:39.240 --> 42:42.710
Glory, glory Hallelujah!-

42:55.880 --> 42:59.634
- I wish I was in Dixie,-
- Hooray! Hooray!-

42:59.840 --> 43:03.515
- In Dixieland I'll take my stand-
- To live and die in Dixie. -

43:03.760 --> 43:11.599
- Away, away, away down South in Dixie,-
- Away, away, away down South in Dixie. -

43:28.160 --> 43:31.869
- I wish I was in Dixie,-
- Hooray! Hooray!-

43:32.120 --> 43:36.033
- In Dixieland I'll take my stand-
- To live and die in Dixie. -

43:36.240 --> 43:43.590
- Away, away, away down South in Dixie,-
- Away, away, away down South in Dixie. -

43:57.360 --> 44:02.388
President, the people demand a victory,
and we've got to take Richmond.

44:10.760 --> 44:14.196
The country is discouraged.
We must do something.

44:14.800 --> 44:17.268
That reminds me of a story...

44:17.760 --> 44:20.479
about a man building
a boat to cross a river.

44:21.160 --> 44:24.311
He got impatient
building the boat and started swimming.

44:25.960 --> 44:27.473
Well, sir, what happened?

44:28.600 --> 44:29.794
He drowned.

44:30.680 --> 44:34.468
We've got to be careful
not to drown this country.

44:45.080 --> 44:46.798
Ready here!
Ready here!

44:48.160 --> 44:49.434
- Quartermaster General.
- Yes, sir.

44:49.640 --> 44:51.039
Ready here!
Ready here!

44:54.000 --> 44:56.150
- Ready here!
- Sergeant, I'm going out.

44:58.800 --> 45:00.791
- How did you make out?
- Make out?

45:01.120 --> 45:02.553
He darned near kissed me.

45:02.680 --> 45:04.238
- Who?
- The Secretary of War.

45:04.480 --> 45:07.472
We're just licking
the tar out of thorn all along the line.

45:08.120 --> 45:09.314
- Who's next?
- I am.

45:09.520 --> 45:12.318
I hope it's for the President.
I'd like to sec his face

45:12.480 --> 45:13.754
when he gets the good news.

45:13.920 --> 45:17.390
Ready here! Commissary.

45:19.000 --> 45:20.831
For General Scott.
Marked private.

45:21.120 --> 45:22.348
Rush it it's victory!

45:27.280 --> 45:28.872
General Scott, what news?

45:29.200 --> 45:31.350
We're winning, sir. I'm sure of it.

45:32.040 --> 45:35.430
- I wish...
- Come in.

45:43.600 --> 45:46.433
Rebel resistance broken at Bulll Run,-

45:46.920 --> 45:50.356
our army sweeping everything before it. -

45:52.440 --> 45:56.274
President, if we can
capture Richmond now,

45:56.520 --> 45:58.431
it means the end of the war.

45:58.600 --> 46:01.353
- Ah, thank God.
- And you, sir...

46:01.960 --> 46:05.555
this victory will silence
your enemies forever

46:06.080 --> 46:09.595
and you will be
the greatest president in our history.

46:09.760 --> 46:13.036
It doesn't matter
what they think of me, General.

46:14.520 --> 46:16.112
- We will have saved the Unión.
- Yes.

46:19.200 --> 46:22.795
General, would you mind
letting me have that telegram?

46:22.880 --> 46:24.950
I'd like to show it
to Mrs. Lincoln myself.

46:25.160 --> 46:27.549
Why, certainly, not, Mr. President.

46:28.520 --> 46:32.115
And would you mind
not calling me 'Mr. President'..

46:33.080 --> 46:34.513
just Lincoln.

46:35.520 --> 46:37.715
All right, Lincoln.

46:45.840 --> 46:48.354
Ready here!
Headquarters!

46:48.760 --> 46:50.990
Sergeant, all messages
for General Scott, hold.

46:51.240 --> 46:52.798
All messages for General Scott hold.

46:53.120 --> 46:54.997
All messages for General Scott hold.

46:55.280 --> 46:57.669
Attentión! Commanding officer.

47:02.080 --> 47:03.354
At ease!

47:03.520 --> 47:04.714
Ready here!

47:05.920 --> 47:08.229
Bad news?
Give it to me.

47:15.640 --> 47:17.471
Attentión the President!

47:18.280 --> 47:19.474
At ease!

47:20.000 --> 47:22.150
Well, General, what news now?

47:24.160 --> 47:25.912
And the first reports?

47:28.040 --> 47:29.871
Over-confidence.

47:32.920 --> 47:34.911
Yes, I should have known.

47:46.360 --> 47:48.555
Impossible to reform lines. -

47:49.600 --> 47:51.591
The men are a confused mob,-

47:52.120 --> 47:53.917
entirely demoralized. -

47:54.520 --> 47:58.399
You must make every effort
to save Washington.

